# Research Result

**Goal:** Prove: for u, v in {1,...,p-2} with u+v not congruent to 0 mod p and u+v != p-1 mod p,
min([u]+[v], [u^{-1}]+[vu^{-1}], [v^{-1}]+[uv^{-1}]) <= p-1.

This is a pure arithmetic statement about F_p. It says: given two "non-antipodal" elements,
at least one of three "inversions" produces a pair summing to at most p-1.

Verified for all (u,v) pairs at p = 5, 7, 11, 13, 17, 19. Zero failures.

This single lemma completes the proof of eta(C_p^3) = 8(p-1)+1.
